-- Euro Erases Declines Against Japanese Yen, Strengthens Versus U.S. Dollar
-- Daniel Tilles
-- 2010-06-15T10:09:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/euro-erases-declines-against-japanese-yen-strengthens-versus-u-s-dollar.html

          
          
             The euro erased its declines against
the yen and strengthened versus the dollar.  
 The 16-nation currency rose 0.1 percent to 112.04 yen as of
11:08 a.m. in London, after weakening to 110.87. The euro
climbed 0.3 percent to $1.2255.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
